solutions.content:
The problem is split in two parts. 
First, compute 2D prefix sum matrix ```ps```, so that element ```p[i][j]``` is equal to the sum of elements in submatrix ```matrix[x][y]``` with ```0 <= x <= i, 0 <= y <= j```. For this purpose we compute 1D prefix sums for the first row and first column and then use the formula:
```ps[i][j] = matrix[i][j] + ps[i-1][j] + ps[i][j-1] - ps[i-1][j-1]```


Here is illustration:
<img src="https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/fad46894-4b59-48a9-a0f8-a6e969cc7b29_1618664366.132954.png" alt="drawing" height="200"/>

The sum of elements from ```(0,0)``` to ```(i,j)``` consists of element ```matrix[i][j]``` and sums of elemnts in submatrices ```A,B,C```. 

Sum of elements in ```A``` is simply ```ps[i-1][j-1]```.
Elements in ```B```: ```ps[i][j-1] - ps[i-1][j-1]```.
Elements in ```C```: ```ps[i-1][j] - ps[i-1][j-1]```.
Summing of all this 

Second part of the solution: use the prefix sum matrix to quickly compute sums of all the possible submatrices:
<img src="https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/1d8e4609-5d06-4ad8-b97e-9f4af78e9906_1618665165.0758274.png" alt="drawing" height="250"/>
Sum of elements in submatrix ```matrix[x][y]``` with ```i0 <= x <= i1, j0 <= y <= j1``` is a difference between elements in ```D``` and elements in ```A```,```B``` and ```C```.  

Sum in ```D``` and ```A``` are prefix sums ```ps[i1][j1]``` and ```ps[i0-1][j0-1]```. For the remaining two submatrices we get:
```B=ps[i1][j0-1] - ps[i0-1][j0-1]```
```C=ps[i0-1][j1] - ps[i0-1][j0-1]```

Hence, the final formula is:
```sum = ps[i1][j1]-ps[i1][j0-1]-ps[i0-1][j1]+ps[i0-1][j0-1]```

The corner cases are when ```j0=0``` or ```i0=0```.

```
class Solution {
    int ps[101][101];
public:
    int numSubmatrixSumTarget(vector<vector<int>>& M, int target) {
        ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false);
        size_t n{ M.size() }, m{ M[0].size() };

		// compute prefix sum
        ps[0][0] = M[0][0];
        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) ps[i][0] = M[i][0] + ps[i-1][0];
        for (int j = 1; j < m; j++) ps[0][j] = M[0][j] + ps[0][j-1];

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++)
            for (int j = 1; j < m; j++)
                ps[i][j] = M[i][j] + ps[i-1][j] + ps[i][j-1] - ps[i-1][j-1];


        int count{};
        // test all submatrices
        for (int i0 = 0; i0 < n; i0++)
            for (int j0 = 0; j0 < m; j0++)
                for (int i1 = i0; i1 < n; i1++)
                    for (int j1 = j0; j1 < m; j1++) {
                        int sum{ ps[i1][j1] };

                        if (i0 > 0) sum -= ps[i0 - 1][j1];
                        if (j0 > 0) sum -= ps[i1][j0-1];
                        if (i0 > 0 && j0 > 0) sum += ps[i0 - 1][j0 - 1];

                        if (sum == target) count++;
                    }

        return count;
    }
};
```

