Firstly make a basic prefix sum DP solution for O(m * m * n * n) time.
```rust
pub fn num_submatrix_sum_target_old(matrix: Vec<Vec<i32>>, target: i32) -> i32 {
    let mut dp = vec![vec![0; matrix[0].len() + 1]; matrix.len() + 1];
    let mut ans = 0;        
    for i in 0..matrix.len() {
        for j in 0..matrix[0].len() {
            dp[i + 1][j + 1] = dp[i + 1][j] + dp[i][j + 1] - dp[i][j] + matrix[i][j];
            for x in 0..i + 1 {
                for y in 0..j + 1 {
                    if dp[i + 1][j + 1] - dp[i + 1][y] - (dp[x][j + 1] - dp[x][y]) == target {
                        ans += 1;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    ans
}
```
Then we can find that the count of previous results of `dp[x][j + 1] - dp[x][y]` can be grouped up with a HashMap. Simple modification but having a O(m * n * n) space HashMap.
```rust
pub fn num_submatrix_sum_target_hash(matrix: Vec<Vec<i32>>, target: i32) -> i32 {
    let mut dp = vec![vec![0; matrix[0].len() + 1]; matrix.len() + 1];
    let mut ans = 0;        
    let mut hash: HashMap<(usize, usize, i32), i32> = HashMap::new();
    for j in 0..matrix[0].len() {
        for y in 0..j + 1 {
            hash.insert((y, j + 1, 0), 1);
        }
    }
    for i in 0..matrix.len() {
        for j in 0..matrix[0].len() {
            dp[i + 1][j + 1] = dp[i + 1][j] + dp[i][j + 1] - dp[i][j] + matrix[i][j];
            for y in 0..j + 1 {
                let diff = dp[i + 1][j + 1] - dp[i + 1][y];
                if let Some(c) = hash.get(&(y, j + 1, diff - target)) {
                    ans += c;
                }
                *hash.entry((y, j + 1, diff)).or_insert(0) += 1;
            }
        }
    }
    ans
}
```
Then optimize the HashMap space usage by eliminating the `(y, j + 1)` part, making it O(n) space.
```rust
pub fn num_submatrix_sum_target(matrix: Vec<Vec<i32>>, target: i32) -> i32 {
    let mut dp = vec![vec![0; matrix[0].len() + 1]; matrix.len() + 1];
    let mut ans = 0;
    for i in 0..matrix.len() {
        for j in 0..matrix[0].len() {
            dp[i + 1][j + 1] = dp[i + 1][j] + dp[i][j + 1] - dp[i][j] + matrix[i][j];
        }
    }
    for j in 0..matrix[0].len() {
        for y in 0..j + 1 {
            let mut hash: HashMap<i32, i32> = HashMap::new();
