solutions.content:
Remebr this from your high school Maths class ?
**n(A∪B) = n(A) + n(B) - n(A∩B)** 
I have tried to use concept of *prefix sum matrix* here(which was the solution for similar problem in 1D array) and *basic concept of set theory (stated above)* to solve a problem which was to efficiently calculate prefix sum matrix.
After that for every possible submatrix we check wether it's sum is equal to target or not and collect our required answer.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int numSubmatrixSumTarget(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int target) {

        // Make the Plan
        int n = matrix.size(), m = matrix[0].size(), ans = 0;
        vector<vector<int> > preSum(n+1,vector<int>(m+1));

        // Execute The Plan
        for ( int i = 0 ; i < n ; ++i ) 
            for ( int j = 0 ; j < m ; ++j ) 
                preSum[i+1][j+1] = matrix[i][j] + preSum[i][j+1] + preSum[i+1][j] - preSum[i][j];

        // Expect the plan to go off the rails
        for ( int x1 = 1 ; x1 < n+1 ; ++x1 )
            for ( int y1 = 1 ; y1 < m+1 ; ++y1 )
                for ( int x2 = x1 ; x2 < n+1 ; ++x2 )
                    for ( int y2 = y1 ; y2 < m+1 ; ++y2 ) 
                        ans += ( preSum[x2][y2] - preSum[x1-1][y2] - preSum[x2][y1-1] + preSum[x1-1][y1-1]==target );

        // Throw the plan
        return ans;
    }
};
```
