solutions.content:
The idea is to flatten one dimension of the array, by obtaining sums of all numbers between each set of two columns.

We can then iterate over every possible range of these sums, to find the target sum.

```
class Solution {
    public int numSubmatrixSumTarget(int[][] matrix, int target) {
        int result = 0;

        int rows = matrix.length;
        if (rows == 0) return 0;

        int cols = matrix[0].length;
        if (cols == 0) return 0;

        for (int ileft = 0; ileft < cols; ileft++) {
            // Contains sum of numbers between ileft and iright
            int[] rowSums = new int[rows];

            for (int iright = ileft; iright < cols; iright++) {

                for (int row = 0; row < rows; row++) {
                    rowSums[row] += matrix[row][iright];
                }

                // Brute force: find all ranges in rowSums that add up to target
                for (int isum = 0; isum < rowSums.length; isum++) {

                    int curSum = 0; 
                    for (int jsum = isum; jsum < rowSums.length; jsum++) {
                        curSum += rowSums[jsum];

                        if (curSum == target) {
                            result++;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

        }

        return result;
    }
}
```

